        <title>Learning THINGS</title>
        <author>
            <name>Craig Macnaughton</name>
        </author>
        <link href="https://www.littlemittenpress.com/learning-things.html"/>
        <id>https://www.littlemittenpress.com/learning-things.html</id>

        <updated>2022-06-07T19:16:43-04:00</updated>
            <summary>
                <![CDATA[
                    A series of picture books for young readers interested in the natural world. A B Sea Creatures: An Astonishing Aquatic&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                
    <figure class="post__image post__image--center">
      <img loading="lazy" src="https://www.littlemittenpress.com/media/posts/2/learning-things-leaf.png" height="123" width="409" alt="Learning THINGS"  sizes="(min-width: 37.5em) 1600px, 80vw" srcset="https://www.littlemittenpress.com/media/posts/2/responsive/learning-things-leaf-xs.png 384w ,https://www.littlemittenpress.com/media/posts/2/responsive/learning-things-leaf-sm.png 600w ,https://www.littlemittenpress.com/media/posts/2/responsive/learning-things-leaf-md.png 768w ,https://www.littlemittenpress.com/media/posts/2/responsive/learning-things-leaf-lg.png 1200w ,https://www.littlemittenpress.com/media/posts/2/responsive/learning-things-leaf-xl.png 1600w">
      
    </figure>

  <p class="align-center">
    <br><b>A series of picture books for young readers interested in the natural world.</b><br><br><a href="https://www.littlemittenpress.com/a-b-sea-creatures-an-astonishing-aquatic-alphabet.html">A B Sea Creatures: An Astonishing Aquatic Alphabet!</a>&nbsp;(October 2019)<br><a href="https://www.littlemittenpress.com/a-b-sea-creatures-an-astonishing-aquatic-alphabet-2.html">Birds of a Letter: ABC Together!</a> (June 2020)<br><a href="https://www.littlemittenpress.com/26-bugs-an-incredible-insect-abc.html">26 Bugs: An Incredible Insect ABC!</a> (November 2021)<br><a href="https://www.littlemittenpress.com/26-bugs-an-incredible-insect-abc-2.html">R is for Rainforests:&nbsp;A Brilliantly Biodiverse Alphabet!</a> (June 2022)
  </p>

  <p>
    Not only does the series introduce core concepts such the ABC’s, but you also get to meet “things” that you may not have ever seen before, from all across the biosphere.
  </p>

  <p>
    The books are built as a jumping off point to more learning and exploring, for example: why does a Northern Pygmy Owl hide its food? Why are Red-Lipped Batfish terrible, terrible swimmers? And why is an Atlas Moth so afraid of its own wings? These are the questions kids need answers to! The colourful illustrations, incredible animals and fun factoids are all designed to pique the curiosity of any reader, young or old.<br>
  </p>

  <p class="align-center">
    <b>Learn about some things, with Learning THINGS!</b><br>
  </p>
            ]]>
        </content>
    </entry>
    <entry>
        <title>About</title>
        <author>
            <name>Craig Macnaughton</name>
        </author>
        <link href="https://www.littlemittenpress.com/about.html"/>
        <id>https://www.littlemittenpress.com/about.html</id>

        <updated>2022-06-27T17:39:30-04:00</updated>
            <summary>
                <![CDATA[
                    An independent Toronto-based publisher of mischievous, creative and thoughtful children’s books. Our name comes from a certain three year old,&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                <h1>An independent Toronto-based publisher of mischievous, creative and thoughtful children’s books.</h1>
<p>Our name comes from a certain three year old, who, despite it being the coldest time of the Canadian winter, continually asks if she could wear her ‘little mittens.’ And yes, a picture book is in the works about the eternal struggle between a daddy and his stubborn daughter.</p>
<figure class="post__image"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://www.littlemittenpress.com/media/posts/1/about-img-05.jpg" alt="" width="945" height="650" sizes="(min-width: 37.5em) 1600px, 80vw" srcset="https://www.littlemittenpress.com/media/posts/1/responsive/about-img-05-xs.jpg 384w ,https://www.littlemittenpress.com/media/posts/1/responsive/about-img-05-sm.jpg 600w ,https://www.littlemittenpress.com/media/posts/1/responsive/about-img-05-md.jpg 768w ,https://www.littlemittenpress.com/media/posts/1/responsive/about-img-05-lg.jpg 1200w ,https://www.littlemittenpress.com/media/posts/1/responsive/about-img-05-xl.jpg 1600w"></figure>
<p><strong><a href="http://www.craigmacnaughton.com">Craig Macnaughton</a></strong> is author, illustrator, picture book maker and the founder of Little Mitten Press. He's also is a stay-at-home-parent, fine artist and film buff. "A B Sea Creatures" was launched in October 2019, with "Birds of a Letter", "26 Bugs" and "R is for Rainforests" following, with many picture books on the way!</p>
<p>Also a budding chef, graphic designer and award-winning filmmaker, Craig is a member of <a href="https://www.12x12challenge.com/">Julie Hedlund’s 12x12 Challenge</a>, <a href="https://canadaeast.scbwi.org/">SCBWI Canada East</a> and <a href="https://www.canscaip.org/">CANSCAIP</a> (Canadian Society of Children's Authors, Illustrators and Performers).</p>
<p>Craig lives in Toronto with his wife and two kids.</p>
